rComments: Awesome prof. Have taken 3 courses with him and SLA256 was clear and easy. Koznarsky gives great feedback on essays and genuinely seems to enjoy getting to read them and see everyones different takes on things. Always willing to give an extension or talk after class for clarity. Only downside is that he is very monotone and can put you to sleep.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Test heavy']

rComments: I've taken a few courses with Professor Koznarsky. They have all been great. Readings are well-chosen--some works I hadn't heard of before have now become my favourites. Lectures are very detailed, but easy to follow and enjoyable to listen to. He gives detailed and helpful feedback on essays, too. I would recommend taking anything he's teaching.

Bad bad prof. Entire course is based on memorization of weird details of random texts which you don't really care about (and not gonna use this knowledge like ever in your life). Tests are tricky and you won't have time to complete all the questions (65 questions in 2 hours? Cmon). One of the hardest courses I took in UofT (I'm in Rotman 4th yr).

Professor Koznarsky is very knowledgeable, but his delivery style can be dry and make it difficult to fully engage with his class. Much of the material he teaches is interesting, but there are a lot of readings and classroom discussions often become tangential.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: One of my favourite profs. He knows his subject inside out. I took Pushkin and learned more than I ever though I would. Not only that, but the readings given (although heavy) were VERY well chosen by him, and very delicately discussed. If you are a fan of Pushkin in general, you will most definitely enjoy this course.

Great Prof really helped me out during his office hours. Lectures were lucid and interesting and got me more heavily into Gogol and the scholarship surrounding him. Highly recommend taking one of his classes
Terrible lecturer. The class was totally content free. I'm a Gogol fan and got a solid mark. Still. Avoid him like the plague.
Took Gogol with him. Got one of the lowest marks although I'm an ace essay writer and I know Gogol like the back of my hand. I think he just picks on certain people.
Very good prof, he's really organized, will help you in his office hours and knows his stuff.  I really can't say anything negative about him.  A must take :).
pretty good prof. explains everything clearly (although a little disorganized, nad doesn't manage his time that good). nice prof overall..
